unittitle.value: Guide to the Faculty Minutes, 1896 - present

abstract.label: Abstract
abstract.value: The Faculty Minutes contain meeting minutes and related documents to Polytechnic faculty meetings. The minutes reflect the name changes of the institution from the Polytechnic Institute of Brooklyn (PIB) to the Polytechnic Institute of New York (PINY) to Polytechnic University, and, finally, to the Polytechnic Institute of New York University.

p.value: The minutes reflect changes in the institution over time, including faculty appointments, graduation lists, proposed and accepted courses, and other issues related to the operation of the university.

The Faculty Minutes contain both meeting minutes and other associated documents from faculty meetings. The minutes span from 1896 to the present and are available as bound items, binders, and loose paper documents.
